headline: Treasury Yields Rise as September Starts at Sober Note
summary: TREASURYS 1539 ET – Treasurys sell off as Wall Street grapples with policy uncertainty, sending yields higher. Manufacturing reports today were lukewarm. JOLTS and the Beige Book are due tomorrow. For Thursday, economists surveyed by WSJ expect ADP job creation at 75,000, down from July’s 104,000.
